                 show="new">letter from Geary to Major General Persifor Smith (WA MSS S-218)</ref>.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
      <bioghist id="aspace_8364f02ab909c12381bfc62e3ca53354">
         <head>JOHN WHITE GEARY (1819-1873)</head>
         <p>John White Geary (1819-1873) served in the Mexican War in the 2d Pennsylvania Infantry, became postmaster at San Francisco in 1849, and held several other public posts in San Francisco. He returned to Pennsylvania in 1852, became governor of Kansas Territory in 1856, but resigned in 1857 and went back to Pennsylvania. Geary served with the 28th Pennsylvania Regiment in the Civil War and was twice elected governor of the state, 1867-1873.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_36aaa35d6498e2c7ef2d0d56f8ac3391">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of business and other correspondence, notes, accounts, and other documents. All letters are to Geary, unless otherwise specified. Additional unsorted papers, including: autograph documents, bonds, photos of Geary, autograph notes, etc., are included in folder marked, "Miscellaneous Material," but have not been listed.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_a99f2e1f12709b991c968ef7f9e0f1fa">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>This collection, listed alphabetically here, is arranged chronologically.</p>  
      </arrangement>
